Loading datasets and shuffling¶

In [ ]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import joblib
# import cv2
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier 
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, accuracy_score, confusion_matrix, roc_curve, auc
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV, KFold
from sklearn.utils import shuffle

train_df = pd.read_csv("emnist-letters-train.csv")
test_df = pd.read_csv("emnist-letters-test.csv")

train_df = shuffle(train_df, random_state=42)
test_df = shuffle(test_df, random_state=42)

train_labels = train_df.iloc[:, 0]
print("Train labels shape: ", train_labels.shape)
train_df = train_df.drop(train_df.columns[0], axis=1)
print("Train_df shape: ", train_df.shape)

test_labels = test_df.iloc[:, 0]
print("test_labels shape: " ,test_labels.shape)
test_df = test_df.drop(test_df.columns[0], axis=1)
print("test_df shape: ", test_df.shape)

for i in range(0, 26):
    mp[i+1] = chr(ord('a') + i)
print(mp)

preprocessing images so all have same orientation and shuffling¶

In [ ]:
train_df = np.array(train_df)
train_df = train_df / 255.0

train_df_image = train_df.reshape((-1, 28, 28, 1)) # adjust on the number of rows, each image is grey 28 * 28
train_df_image = np.rot90(train_df_image, axes=(1, 2))
train_df_image = np.flip(train_df_image, axis=1)

test_df = np.array(test_df)
test_df = test_df / 255.0

test_df_image = test_df.reshape((-1, 28, 28, 1))
test_df_image = np.rot90(test_df_image, axes=(1, 2))
test_df_image = np.flip(test_df_image, axis=1)

Drawing images function¶

In [ ]:
def draw_images(images, row_count, column_count):
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(row_count, column_count, figsize=(10,10))
    for i in range(row_count):
        for j in range(column_count):
            axs[i,j].imshow(images[i * column_count + j], cmap="gray")
            axs[i,j].axis('off')
    plt.show()

indices = np.random.choice(train_df_image.shape[0], 300) # choose from 0 to 88798 (shape[0]) 300 element
draw_images(train_df_image[indices].squeeze(), 15, 15)

from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelBinarizer
y_score = best_model.predict_proba(test_df)
print("Train labels: ")
print(pd.DataFrame(train_labels).value_counts())
print("----------------------------------------------------------------------------")
print(pd.DataFrame(y_score).value_counts())
print("y_score_proba: shape ", y_score.shape)
print("----------------------------------------------------------------------------")
print("Pred labels: ")
print(pd.DataFrame(pred_labels).value_counts())
print("----------------------------------------------------------------------------")
print("test_labels: ")
print(pd.DataFrame(test_labels).value_counts())
print("----------------------------------------------------------------------------")
print("train_labels: ")
print(pd.DataFrame(train_labels).value_counts())
print("----------------------------------------------------------------------------")
print("train_labels: ")
print(np.array(train_labels.shape))

label_binarizer = LabelBinarizer()
y_bin = label_binarizer.fit_transform(test_labels)

print(y_score.shape, y_bin.shape, y_bin[0], test_labels.shape)
fpr = dict()
tpr = dict()
roc_auc = dict()
n_classes = 26
for i in range(1, 20):
    fpr[i], tpr[i], _ = roc_curve(y_bin[:, i-1], y_score[:, i-1])
    roc_auc[i] = auc(fpr[i], tpr[i])

# Plot ROC curves
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
for i in range(1, 20):
    plt.plot(fpr[i], tpr[i], label=f'Class {mp[i]} (AUC = {roc_auc[i]:.2f})')

plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--', lw=2)  # Diagonal line for random classifier
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate (FPR)')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate (TPR)')
plt.title('ROC Curve for Each Class (One-vs-All)')
plt.legend(loc='lower right')
plt.show()
